Sidney Wood

Computer Engineering Student | Developer | Robotics Enthusiast

Email: Sidney.scott.wood@gmail.com

Phone: (647)-542-3540 | Location: Toronto, ON

About Me

I am a Computer Engineering student at York University with a passion for robotics, software development, and practical engineering solutions. My experience spans software for robotics, hackathons, and hands-on engineering.

Projects

MTG Win Tracker (Magic: The Gathering)

A full-stack Flask and MySQL web app to track Commander (EDH) match outcomes. Built a dynamic Elo ranking system for both players and decks. Hosted on a Raspberry Pi with Git automation and Nginx for remote access. Allows win/loss tracking, player and deck performance analysis, and historical data review.

Spiri Robotics Intern Projects

Developed real-time sound detection and AIS tracking systems for drone-assisted maritime monitoring. Built Gazebo simulation environments and contributed to SDK and website development for drone control.

Sumobot (YURS)

Designed and programmed a sumobot for competitions. Gained experience in Arduino, sensor integration, and self-driving logic through weekly robotics society workshops.

Skills

  • Python (3 Years): Data Analysis, Automation, APIs
  • Java (4 Years): OOP, Arduino Projects
  • Dart (1 Year): Web/App Design
  • Fusion 360 (2 Years): CAD for Robotics
  • Git (2 Years): Collaborative Dev, Open Source
  • Figma (1 Year): UI/UX Design

Education

York University (2023–2028)

B.Eng. (Honours), Computer Engineering

Courses: Applied Calculus, Discrete Math, Computer Architecture, Mechatronics, OOP, Engineering Mechanics

Hackathons & Competitions

  • Roborama Hackathon (Feb 2024): Self-driving robot in a 12-hour team competition.
  • UNHack (Oct 2023): Developed solutions to UN sustainability goals in a 48-hour sprint.
